The fired employee took revenge, bought laptops for the company and sold them
The disgruntled employee, after his dismissal, bought computers at the company and then sold them.
He spent the money before he was arrested by the police.
In a short time, the man bought a total of sixteen computers in twelve cases for more than two hundred thousand crowns.
"He took the laptops to Olomouc after taking over, where he sold them by bazaars," said the chief commissioner of the Šumperk police, Rostislav Brückner.
The motive for the fraud was revenge on the employer for dismissal and also the profit of money.
"During the interrogation, he told us that he used the money for loan payments," Brückner said.
Police also found that the fraudster was a pathological player who had repeatedly been treated for psychiatry.
The money could also end up in slot machines or video lottery terminals.
"The fact is, we didn't find any money with him," the commissioner said.
A fraudster who has already been punished once for theft now faces between one and five years in prison.
Police have not yet said whether there is a risk of punishment also for bazaars, which bought the laptops below the price and continued to sell them.
"It is true that they were taking over completely new goods, which is at least suspicious," the commissioner said.
None of the owners of the bazaar have yet been charged.
